Cell.Text: [S] G|I'll stay here. You try not to get into too much trouble.
[S] G|As you wish. Just don't forget about me.
[S] G|Here? Right here? Very well, J'zargo shall wait.
[S] G|All right. Don't take too long.
[S] G|You sure? All right. I'll keep guard here.
[S] G|Don't make me wait too long. I get bored very easily.
[S] G|Patience isn't exactly my strong suit, but alright.
[S] G|I'll be right here. Be careful now!
[S] G|I'm yours to command, Thane. I'll wait here until you need me.
[S] G|Don't be long. My place is by your side.
[S] G|I will remain on guard here.
[S] G|I'll wait here. Just don't start any trouble without me.
[S] G|Head on, then. I'll keep an eye out.
[S] G|You sure? Fine. I'll stand watch.
[S] G|Go on ahead. I'll stand guard.
[S] G|If that is what you wish.
[S] G|J'zargo is ready for more adventure.
[S] G|Try not to walk into any spike-filled pits or filthy skeever dens.
[S] G|I am the shadow at your back.
[S] G|Good! Let's go find something to fight.
[S] G|My blade is yours to command, Thane.
[S] G|As you will, my Thane. I will protect you with my life.
I need you to come with me.
[S] G|I'd best get back to Master Neloth then. No telling what's happened since I've been gone.
[S] G|You'll be all right on your own? Then I'll see you back at the College.
[S] G|Really? J'zargo was having such fun. Ah, well. Back to the College then.
[S] G|I understand. We must all follow our own paths. If you wish to find me again, I'll be in Nightcaller Temple.
[S] G|Such a shame. I thought we were getting along so well. I'll head back to Riften if you should have second thoughts.
[S] G|Farewell, then. If you need my services again, just come and look for me in the usual place.
[S] G|So you think you can make it on your own, then? We'll just see about that.
[S] G|If that's what you want. Watch your back out there, and if you need me again, you know where I'll be.
[S] G|It is a lonely thing, facing all the dangers of Skyrim by yourself. Come and find me if you decide that you miss my companionship.
[S] G|You're letting me go? What's wrong, is my skill with a blade making you look bad? Hah! I'm kidding, friend. Until we meet again!
[S] G|Well, it's been fun. I guess I'll head back to Rorikstead.
[S] G|I will be back at your house if you need me, Thane.
[S] G|I'll keep watch at Lakeview Manor until you return, Thane. Good hunting.
[S] G|I'll return to Windstad Manor and remain on guard, my Thane.
[S] G|As you command, Thane. I'll guard Heljarchen House until you return.
[S] G|I'll wait for you at the Jarl's Longhouse in Falkreath until you need me again, Thane.
[S] G|I'll return to Highmoon Hall in Morthal until you need me again, Thane.
[S] G|As you command, Thane. I'll wait at the White Hall in Dawnstar until you need me again.
It's time for you to go back home, dog.
[S] G|I'll head back home if you need me.
[S] G|Then back home is where you'll find me.
[S] G|I'll be heading home, then, if you need me.
[S] G|You need my strength again, I'll be home.
[S] G|I'm heading home if you need me.
[S] G|I need to get back to the village. My father will have need of me.
[S] G|Well, then, I'm going to head back and get myself a drink. Maybe I'll see you soon.
[S] G|It has been an honor, Skaal-friend.

Node.Caption: DialogueFollowerDismissTopic: It's time for us to part ways.

Cell.Text: [S] I'm a mage, not a pawnbroker, you know.
[S] If it will help you, then certainly.
[S] J'zargo only has so much room to carry things.
[S] No problem, I can carry a good bit of gear.
[S] Running out of room, eh? I'll be glad to help.
[S] Do I get to keep it? Just kidding.
[S] I am an apprentice wizard, not a pack mule! Oh very well, but make it quick.
[S] Sure, feel free to hand me all the gold you want.
[S] If that is what you wish.
[S] No problem! How can I help?
[S] Of course, Thane. How can I be of service?
[S] Do you need something from me, Thane? Or can I carry something for you?
[S] I am sworn to carry your burdens.
[S] How can I serve you, my Thane?
[S] What do you want me to carry?
[S] I'll shoulder some of your burden.
[S] What do you need to take?

Node.Caption: DialogueFollowerTradeTopic: I need to trade some things with you.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Anything, as long as I get to fight.
[S] G|What would you ask of me?
[S] G|Just let me know what needs doing.

Node.Caption: DialogueFollowerFavorStateTopic: I need you to do something.

Cell.Text: You want me to do something or not?
Still something you'd like me to do?
Did you require something of J'zargo?
Did you still need me for something?
So, did you still need my assistance?
Still need me to do something?
Do you still need me to do something?
You wanted me to do something, yes?
You still wish something of me?
Is there still something you need of me?
What was it you needed, again?
Here, boy. Let me show you what I need.
Never mind, boy. I don't need you to do anything.
